Willie RINDNER, Bankrupt, v. Harry B. ROSENBAUM, as Trustee, etc., Appellant. No. 189. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 20, 1933. Weinberg & Weinberg, of New York City (Benjamin Weiss and Reuben Weinberg, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Sarafite & Naftalison, of New York City (Louis J. Naftalison and Joseph A. Sarafite, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellees. Samuel Weisman, of New York City, for bankrupt.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
